PrecisRegulations Amending the ONTARIO FISHERY REGULATIONS, 1989 which make minor administrative amendments as well as adjust the number of lines for ice fishing, create new sanctuaries to protect spawning adults, limit the number of bait-fish allowed in one's possession, establish daily catch limits for crappie and yellow perch in northwestern Ontario, and adjust lake specific quotas, effective January 1, 2000.
